   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Commissioned development policy research 2010</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Commissioned development policy research 2010. The purpose of the commissioned development policy research is to support the planning, decision making and implementation of Finland&apos;s development policy and development cooperation. The research is based on the information needs of the Ministry. The approach and particular emphasis of the projects are discussed with the researchers, without hampering their academic freedom. The duration of projects varies between 3-12 months. Each project is supported by a Steering Group consisting of sector and area experts. The results of projects are discussed in public seminars with the research community, civil servants and civil society actors.</narrative>
  </description>
